","n31179","n31180"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D8%B9%D9%8E%D9%8A%D9%8E%D9%91%D8%AF%D9%8E"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"noun","gloss":"feast; holiday; festival","examples":[{"text":"يَتَبَادَلُ النَّاسُ التَّهَانِي وَالْهَدَايَا فِي أَيَّامِ الْعِيدِ.","english":"People exchange greetings and gifts during the holiday."}]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"festivity; gala; carnival"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to hold a feast"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to celebrate"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to congratulate (someone) on the occasion of a feast"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"plural of عَادَة (ʕāda)","tags":["form-of","plural"]}]},"etymology":{"source":"wiktextract","text":"Denominal verb from عِيد (ʕīd, “festival”)."},"ipa":["/ʕiːd/","/ʕaj.ja.da/","/ʕi.jad/"],"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n30939","headword_ar":"عِيدٌ","root":"Ewd","body":[{"kind":"text","text":", originally"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EiwodN","text_ar":"عِوْدٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"w","text_ar":"و"},{"kind":"text","text":"being changed into"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Y","text_ar":"ى"},{"kind":"text","text":"because of the kesreh before it, (Az, TA,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"An occurrence that befalls,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"betides, one,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"that happens to one,"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"returns to one,"},{"kind":"text","text":"of some former affection of the mind or body, i. e.] of anxiety, (S, O, K,) or of some other kind, (S, O,) of disease, or of grief, (O, K,) and the like, (K,) of affliction, and of desire: and accord. to Az, the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"time of return"},{"kind":"text","text":"of joy and of grief. (TA.) ―         -b2-  [And hence,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A festival;"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"periodical festival;"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a feast-day;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(KL;)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"i. q."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mawosimN","text_ar":"مَوْسِمٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (Msb;)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"any day on which is an assembling,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a congregating;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K;) [and particularly"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"an anniversary festival:"},{"kind":"text","text":"] so called because it returns every year with renewed joy: (IAar, TA:) or, from"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EaAda","text_ar":"عَادَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", because people return to it: or from"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EaAdapN","text_ar":"عَادَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", “ a custom,” because they are accustomed to it: (TA:) pl."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aEoyaAdN","text_ar":"اَعْيَادٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Y","text_ar":"ى"},{"kind":"text","text":"being retained in the pl. because it is in the sing., or to distinguish it from"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aEowaAdN","text_ar":"اَعْوَادٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"the pl. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EuwdN","text_ar":"عُودٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (S, O, Msb;) for regularly its pl. would be"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aEowaAdN","text_ar":"اَعْوَادٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", like as"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^arowaAHN","text_ar":"اَرْوَاحٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is pl. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"riyHN","text_ar":"رِيحٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (TA.) [The two principal religious festivals of the Muslims are called"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Eiydu AlA^aDoHaY","text_ar":"عِيدُ الاَضْحَى"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The festival of the victims"},{"kind":"text","text":"(see art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"DHw","text_ar":"ضحو"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"DHY","text_ar":"ضحى"},{"kind":"text","text":") and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Eiydu AlfiTori","text_ar":"عِيدُ الفِطْرِ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The festival of the breaking of the fast"},{"kind":"text","text":"after Ramadán.] The dim. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EiydN","text_ar":"عِيدٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EuyayodN","text_ar":"عُيَيْدٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"; the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Y","text_ar":"ى"},{"kind":"text","text":"being retained in it like as it is retained in the pl. (TA.) ―         -b3-  See also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EaAdapN","text_ar":"عَادَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", in two places.       -A2-  Also,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A certain sort of mountain-tree,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K, TA,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"that produces twigs about a cubit in length, dust-"},{"kind":"page_break","n":2191},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"coloured, having no leaves nor blossoms, but having much peel, and having many knots: fresh wounds are dressed with its peel, and close up in consequence thereof."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.)"}],"source_refs":["Az","TA","S","O","K","IAar"]},{"entry_id":"n31179","headword_ar":"عيّد","root":"Quasi Eyd","body":[{"kind":"text","text":": see 2 in art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Ewd","text_ar":"عود"},{"kind":"text","text":"."}],"source_refs":[]},{"entry_id":"n31180","headword_ar":"عِيّدٌ","root":"Quasi Eyd","body":[{"kind":"text","text":": and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Eiydiy~apN","text_ar":"عِيدِيَّةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":": and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EayodaAnN","text_ar":"عَيْدَانٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":": and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EuyayodN","text_ar":"عُيَيْدٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":": see art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Ewd","text_ar":"عود"},{"kind":"text","text":"."}],"source_refs":[]}]}}